  <h2>What the PHP 2.25 trillion figure represents</h2>

  <p>Cumulative payouts is not revenue and it is not gross gaming yield. It is the total peso value returned to players across all BingoPlus games since launch, which includes wagers won back through normal game outcomes, jackpot prizes, and bonus payouts. In a high-volume electronic bingo product, cumulative payouts can run an order of magnitude larger than gross gaming revenue, because each player's deposit can be wagered, won, and re-wagered multiple times before any net amount is recognized on either side of the ledger.</p>

  <p>What the figure does signal cleanly is throughput. PHP 2.25 trillion of money moving through the player layer of a single PAGCOR-licensed e-Games platform demonstrates that BingoPlus has reached a scale where its activity meaningfully sits inside the broader Philippine consumer finance picture. For comparison, the entire Philippine gross gaming revenue for Q1 2026 was approximately PHP 88 billion across all licensed operators and license types combined.</p>

  <h2>The user-base story</h2>

  <p>The 3 million verified users figure is what BingoPlus is pointing investors toward. Every one of those users has cleared the platform's KYC pipeline, which in DigiPlus's case is integrated with the company's standard verification infrastructure used across ArenaPlus, BingoPlus, and PeryaGame. The 2.9 million active daily users number is closer to a true engagement measure &mdash; it suggests that the gap between registered and active is tighter on BingoPlus than is typical of mass-market consumer apps in the Philippine market.</p>

  <p>The activity metrics surfaced at the anniversary fill in the engagement picture. BingoPlus disclosed 214,852 average daily user interactions and 628,459 gaming actions driven by in-platform engagement features. The platform's content creator program counted 11,437 active creators producing 17,854 posts in the disclosure window. Together, these numbers describe a platform that has built a sticky surface around its core gaming product, not just a bingo room with players in and out.</p>

  <div class="pull-quote">
    <p>"What the cumulative payout number does is shift the conversation. We are no longer asking whether digital bingo can scale in the Philippine market. We are asking what scale this segment can hold."</p>
    <cite>Gaming sector equity analyst tracking DigiPlus, speaking on background, May 2026</cite>
  </div>

  <h2>The DigiPlus context</h2>

  <p>BingoPlus is the largest component of DigiPlus Interactive Corp.'s domestic platform business, and the platform's performance is central to DigiPlus's investor narrative. DigiPlus posted full-year 2025 net income of PHP 12.6 billion on revenue of PHP 84.2 billion, with EBITDA of PHP 14.2 billion. The board approved a PHP 3.8 billion cash dividend equal to 30 percent of consolidated net income attributable to shareholders.</p>

  <p>The 2025 results carried an asterisk. Strong first-half momentum was partially offset by the impact of the third-quarter delinking of direct e-wallet auto-pay access to licensed gaming platforms, a structural payment-rails change that DigiPlus management described as testing the loyalty of its core user base. Management's response, articulated at the anniversary, has been to position BingoPlus's verified-user footprint and content-creator ecosystem as the durable moat that survives payment-channel disruption.</p>

  <p>BingoPlus's record single-day payout of PHP 935,262,012 on June 6, 2025 sits in the pre-delinking period and serves as the high-water mark for daily throughput on the platform. The platform has not yet disclosed a comparable post-delinking high-water mark, and the omission has been noted by analysts watching the recovery curve.</p>

  <h2>The community-investment overlay</h2>

  <p>DigiPlus's anniversary disclosure also emphasized the DigiPlus Foundation footprint, with PHP 84.2 million invested across 57 community programs reaching 976,759 beneficiaries. The figures are part of the company's positioning around responsible gaming and social license &mdash; both of which are increasingly material to PAGCOR's licensing posture under the 2026 framework.</p>

  <p>The pattern across the Philippine gaming sector is that operator-level community-investment disclosures are becoming a regular feature of investor and regulator-facing communications, on roughly the same arc that ESG disclosures have followed in other Asian consumer-finance verticals. BingoPlus's anniversary report is consistent with that pattern.</p>

  <h2>What the anniversary did not address</h2>

  <p>The disclosure was notably quiet on several questions that the analyst community has been asking. There was no detailed update on the cohort behavior of users acquired before versus after the third-quarter 2025 e-wallet delinking. There was no breakdown of the verified-user base by deposit-tier segmentation. And there was no disclosure of how the PHP 2.25 trillion cumulative payout figure breaks down across the games portfolio &mdash; whether Super Ace and its derivative jackpot variants account for a disproportionate share, or whether the distribution is broader across the catalog.</p>

  <p>These omissions are unsurprising for a marketing-facing anniversary event. They are also the questions that will most likely shape DigiPlus's H1 2026 earnings communication when the company reports later in the quarter.</p>

  <h2>The bottom line</h2>

  <p>BingoPlus has converted the 2026 anniversary into the cleanest single demonstration to date that DigiPlus's flagship platform sits at the scale where it materially shapes the Philippine consumer gaming market. The PHP 2.25 trillion cumulative-payout figure, the 3 million verified-user count, and the 2,482 million-peso jackpot wins are each substantial in their own right and collectively describe a product that has graduated from category leader to category-defining.</p>

  <p>The next test for BingoPlus will arrive with DigiPlus's H1 2026 earnings disclosure, when the post-delinking growth curve becomes visible in the operating numbers rather than in the marketing communications. Until then, the anniversary numbers are the cleanest available read on a platform that has already become impossible to discuss the Philippine gaming sector without.</p>

